metadata.name: Copenhagen Interpretation #44
metadata.description:
The Copenhagen Interpretation of quantum physics suggests that objects don't have physical properties until being observed.

In this generative piece by itsgalo and Sp√∏gelsesmaskinen, a set of objects are being held in "superposition" and finally positioned when observed and minted.

Use mouse/touch to zoom, pan, and rotate. Press 's' to grab a screenshot. Best viewed in Firefox.

metadata.name: Protein Pelt #6
metadata.description:
An incorrectly placed decimal point led to this pattern. A good friend told me it reminded them of protein structures, I found them to look like animal pelts strewn about.

Each "protein" is made up of 100 pelts, random walking around the canvas from the center. Each "pelt" is made of 5 colors sampled from an array of 84 colors.

Press 's' when in live view to save the image.

metadata.name: Lucidity #240
metadata.description:
An abstract depiction of thought. Designed to represent the thinking process of creating artwork.

Made in P5js.

metadata.name: Microgravity #578
metadata.description:
Microgravity is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at The Ever-Evolving World of Art, Art Basel Hong-Kong, 2022.

Scale symmetry of abstract semiliquid forms.

Click on a section of the image to explore deeper.
- Use keys [0-9] to change the detail level.
- Use the "S" key to save a PNG image.
- Use the "R" key to reset the coordinates.

metadata.name: A Stitch Is Fine #18
metadata.description:
Favorites are held together with stitching. Deep weaves of fabric. A patch of solid color. Intricate patterns created by layers of thread.

There are no rarity attributes assigned to this artwork, its value is intended to be determined by viewer aesthetic alone.

This artwork was created using p5js.

linktr.ee/lisaorthstudio
twitter: @lisaorthstudio

metadata.name: Orbs #23
metadata.description:
Serene orbs,
Playfully dynamic,
Soft visceral airy bodies,
Bold, colorful, at once moving, still, tiny, colossal,
Intimate organized chaos, both calm and ethereally energetic

(Created with p5.js and a WEBGL shader.)

metadata.name: Merkki #60
metadata.description:
Merkki is an exploration of primitive forms, randomness and bold lines.
Drawing inspiration from mid-70s iconic single-color logotypes, this project revolves heavily around constraints and minimalism.

- 5 different shape types
- 3 grid sizes
- Mostly monochrome, with occasional color accents
